fields.name: AutoUpgradeMinorVersion
fields.description: Indicates whether the extension should use a newer minor version if one is available at deployment time. Once deployed, however, the extension will not upgrade minor versions unless redeployed, even with this property set to true.

fields.name: ForceUpdateTag
fields.description: If a value is provided and is different from the previous value, the extension handler will be forced to update even if the extension configuration has not changed.

fields.name: ProtectedSettings
fields.description: The extension can contain either protectedSettings or protectedSettingsFromKeyVault or no protected settings at all.

fields.name: ProvisionAfterExtensions
fields.description: Collection of extension names after which this extension needs to be provisioned.

fields.name: ProvisioningState
fields.description: The provisioning state, which only appears in the response.

fields.name: Publisher
fields.description: The name of the extension handler publisher.

fields.name: Settings
fields.description: Json formatted public settings for the extension.

fields.name: Type
fields.description: Specifies the type of the extension; an example is "CustomScriptExtension".

fields.name: TypeHandlerVersion
fields.description: Specifies the version of the script handler.
